  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<strong>Sorcerer Bloodline</strong><br/><br/><p>A scion of forgotten kings, with a lineage rich with the dust of ancient empires spanning every golden age of humanity's history, an imperious embodies the apex of human potential, as well as human temerity and uninhibited hubris.</p><p><b>Race: </b>Human Only</p><p><b>Class Skill: </b>Perform (oratory).</p><p><b>Bonus Spells: </b>moment of greatness (3rd), eagle's splendor (5th), heroism (7th), threefold aspect (9th), greater command (11th), repulsion (13th), greater age resistance (15th), prediction of failure (17th), overwhelming presence (19th).</p><p><b>Bonus Feats: </b>Diehard, Endurance, Heroic Defiance, Heroic Recovery, Improved Initiative, Lingering Spell, Magical Aptitude, Persuasive.</p><p><b>Bloodline Arcana: </b>Whenever you cast a harmful spell, you gain a bonus equal to the spell's level on Intimidate checks made against any creature adversely effected by that spell until the end of your next turn. Adversely effected typically means damage, but it can also mean debilitating effects or conditions.</p><p><b>Bloodline Powers: </b>You draw upon ancestors both legendary and forgotten.</p>",
